{"article_id":"CJ7rxBIJjpPsHzY2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"California Democratic Gov . Jerry Brown is appealing a recent state judge ' s ruling","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that ends tenure and other union protections for public school teachers .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"The appeal was filed late Friday","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"and argues","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"that Los Angeles County Superior Court Judge Rulf Treu ' s final ruling lacks detail","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"and fails to provide the legal basis for his decision .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"Treu issued the final ruling Thursday ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"after tentatively ruling in June","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"that tenure protections for California teachers violate the state constitution ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"depriving some of the state 's 6.2 million students of a quality education , specifically minorities and those from low-income families .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"The lawsuit , Vergara v. California , was brought by Beatriz Vergara and eight other students","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"who said","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"they were saddled with teachers","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"who let classrooms get out of control ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"came to school unprepared","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"and in some cases told them","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"they 'd never make anything of themselves .","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"Teachers and their lawyers argue","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"the laws protect teachers from getting fired on a whim .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"They also argue","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"the system preserved academic freedom","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and helps attract talented teachers to a profession","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that does n't pay well .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Brown ' s appeal states","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"that school districts were for `` unclear and unexplained '' reasons dismissed from the lawsuit ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"which means the court 's decision `` applies only to parties","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that have no role or duties under the challenged lawsuits . ''","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"The appeal also criticizes Treu","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"for simply making his tentative decision final ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"instead of elaborating","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"and expanding on the tentative ruling in June .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"California 's Superintendent of Public Instruction Tom Torlakson ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"who was among those named in a lawsuit ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"asked state Attorney General Kamala Harris to file the appeal","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"because he lacked the legal authority .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"The state 's two biggest teacher unions are also expected to file an appeal ,","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"according to The Los Angeles Times .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"The trial represented the latest battle in a nationwide movement","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"to toughen the standards","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"for granting teachers permanent employment protection and seniority-based preferences during layoffs .","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"Students in New York recently filed a high-profile suit similar to the one in California .","depth":4},{"id":41,"text":"And dozens of states ,","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"including Louisiana and New Jersey ,","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"have moved in recent years to get rid of such protections","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"or raise the standards","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"for obtaining them .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Judge Treu has declined to tell the state Legislature exactly how to change the system ,","depth":4},{"id":47,"text":"but he has expressed confidence","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"it will do so in a way","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that passes constitutional muster .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Torlakson also says","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"the ruling is n't supported by facts or law","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"and is too vague","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"to guide state lawmakers in making alterations .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"Torlakson ,","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"who has union backing","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"as he seeks reelection this fall ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"said","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"teachers were being blamed unfairly for failings in the educational system .","depth":4},{"id":59,"text":"`` We do not fault doctors","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"when the emergency room is full , \"","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"We do not criticize the firefighter","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"whose supply of water runs dry .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Yet","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"while we crowd our classrooms","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"and fail to properly equip them with adequate resources ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"those","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"who filed and support this case","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"shamelessly seek to blame teachers","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"who step forward every day","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"to make a difference for our children . ''","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":143,"left":117,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":108,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":102,"right":107,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":81,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":81,"left":77,"right":80,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":73,"right":76,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":2,"right":75,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":75,"left":3,"right":74,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":74,"left":